article.headline: Duquesne 21, St. Francis, Pa. 7
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- Connor Dixon threw three touchdown passes -- including a 91-yarder -- in the second quarter to lead Duquesne to a 21-7 victory over St. Francis, Pa. on Saturday night. The win gave the Dukes their first victory as a member of the Northeastern Conference. Dixon threw touchdown passes of 12 yards to Alex Roberson and 9 yards to Michael Rasky early in the second quarter. Then, with Duquesne (1-1, 1-0 Northeast Conference) pinned deep in its own territory after a Red Flash turnover in the final seconds before halftime, Dixon found Conrad Carter streaking down the left sideline for a 91-yard scoring strike just before the break. Dixon finished 13-for-25 for 211 yards and completed all five of his attempts in the second quarter for 150 yards. Calvin Williams got St. Francis (0-3, 0-1) on the board in the first quarter with a 9-yard touchdown run. But the Red Flash were hurt by George Little's three interceptions, two of which were made by Chidozie Oparanozie deep in Duquesne territory.
